        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 4 at 11:39PM CDT until June 5 at 12:45AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Armstrong County in the Panhandle of Texas...
East central Randall County in the Panhandle of Texas...
South central Carson County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 1245 AM CDT.

* At 1138 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Palo Duro
Canyon, or 15 miles east of Canyon, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Ping pong ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Claude and Palo Duro Canyon.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
